{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"page_content": "What are the criteria for BUV Mobility Merit Scholarship Award? / Ti\u00eau ch\u00ed \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ec1 c\u1eed ph\u1ea7n th\u01b0\u1edfng ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\u00ecnh h\u1ecdc/tr\u1ea3i nghi\u1ec7m qu\u1ed1c t\u1ebf do BUV t\u00e0i tr\u1ee3 l\u00e0 g\u00ec?\n\nAnswer / C\u00e2u tr\u1ea3 l\u1eddi:\n\nThe number of nominees and awardees within Staffordshire University programmes to gain a sponsored mobility programme award in the UK is 02 students per year.\n\nTo achieve the award, the students must fulfill the following criteria:\n\nThe nominees and awardees must be current and active students in BUV;\n\nThe nominees and awardees must be in Year 2 Semester 1 or Year 2 Semester 2 or Year 3 Semester 1 at the time of selection.\n\nThe 02 nominees and awardees must have the highest cohort's average scores of the previous academic year;\n\nThe 02 nominees and awardees have no Academic Misconduct and no violation of BUV Student Code of Conduct that led to disciplinary decision of temporary suspension or higher.\n\nS\u1ed1 l\u01b0\u1ee3ng sinh vi\u00ean ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\u00ecnh h\u1ecdc do SU c\u1ea5p b\u1eb1ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ec1 c\u1eed ph\u1ea7n th\u01b0\u1edfng tham gia m\u1ed9t ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\u00ecnh h\u1ecdc/tr\u1ea3i nghi\u1ec7m \u1edf n\u01b0\u1edbc ngo\u00e0i do BUV t\u00e0i tr\u1ee3 l\u00e0 02 sinh vi\u00ean m\u1ed7i n\u0103m.\n\n\u0110\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ph\u1ea7n th\u01b0\u1edfng n\u00e0y, sinh vi\u00ean ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u00e1p \u1ee9ng c\u00e1c ti\u00eau ch\u00ed sau:\n\n02 sinh vi\u00ean \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ec1 c\u1eed ph\u1ea3i l\u00e0 sinh vi\u00ean hi\u1ec7n \u0111ang ti\u1ebfp t\u1ee5c ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\u00ecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1ea1i BUV;\n\n02 sinh vi\u00ean \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ec1 c\u1eed ph\u1ea3i \u0111ang h\u1ecdc n\u0103m 2 h\u1ecdc k\u1ef3 1 ho\u1eb7c n\u0103m 2 h\u